@node ARCHIVE
@title "Blocnotes: ArchiveNote.rexx"

@{b} Archivenote.rexx@{ub}

   This script simply makes the active note not screen-fixed, not autoopen,
   and it hides it. Its purpose is to "archive" the note for later use.

@endnode

@node NOTE2WB
@title "Blocnotes: Note2WB.rexx"

@{b} Note2WB.rexx@{ub}

   If you have a note on a public screen and want to move it on Workbench
   screen(maybe to close the screen without hiding the note) just launch
   this script. It will close the window and then reopen it on WB.

@endnode

@node ONDATE
@title "Blocnotes: OnDateStartup.rexx"

@{b} OnDateStartup.rexx@{ub}

   This script was created to use the STARTUP tooltype. It's an example
   of what is possible with it.
   This arexx script could be, of course, started at any time, but the
   best way to use it is to specify the tooltype:
      STARTUP=ondatestartup.rexx

   It simply search through notes for any occurence of the sequence:
    $ONDATE <date in your locale format>
   if the date correspond to the actual date, the notes is showed.
   It's so possible to use BN as a reminder: insert in a note the sequence
   with the date you want it to appear, and hide it (with HideNote.rexx).
   It will be showed automatically that day.

@endnode

